According to the South African Chinese Network, on the morning of April 10, local time, about 10 kilometers from the city of Rustenburg in the North West Province of South Africa, a case of vicious robbery against the Chinese people took place. When the three robbers robbed their belongings and left, they stabbed a Chinese woman who did not revolt with a knife. The wounded died after being rescued. On the morning of the incident, they opened a store as usual. However, three gangsters robbed the shop shortly after. Two gunmen and one knife. The surveillance video showed that during the robbery, the victim Weng Mou did not show any resistance, and the gangster stabbed her chest with a knife when he left, and then was unfortunately killed because of his injuries. This is the first case of Chinese killings in South Africa since the beginning of this year. 